Mrs Sylvia Utete-MasangoVusumuzi Dube, Social Media EditorTHE government has said there will be no two day holiday for schools in Bulawayo and Matabeleland South as had been announced earlier. Permanent Secretary in the Ministry of Primary and Secondary Education Dr Sylvia Utete-Masango said: It has been agreed that schools go ahead as usual.We have consulted with the provincial education offices and it has been noted that there is no need for schools to close as delegates to the 21st February Movement will only start arriving after 4pm on Friday and by then most schools would have long knocked off, said Dr Utete-Masango.More details to follow&#8230;&nbsp;